These six ages, during which the faithful labour for God in this world, correspond with the six days of God’s labour in the works of Creation. The seventh age, answering to His sabbath rest, is that in which the souls of the faithful, separated from their bodies, rest from their labours in the unseen world, and is therefore contemporary with all the other six, beginning when God’s first martyr Abel was slain, and lasting till the general resurrection, when the 501115 of the faithful being united to their glorious bodies, the eighth age begins, which lasis for ever ².
